button.description:
## Description
Bouton d'action interactif multi-variantes (`primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `danger`) et multi-tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`), rendu en élément `<button>` natif avec états `hover`, `active`, `focus` et `disabled`.

## Spec
- **Border-radius** : `8px` sur toutes les variantes et tailles (Figma `cornerRadius: 8.0px`)
- **Tailles** : sm `25px` (padding 4/16px, gap 4px, font 14px) · md `35px` (padding 8/16px, gap 8px, font 16px) · lg `38px` (padding 8/24px, gap 8px, font 18px)
- **Typographie** : Inter, `font-weight: 600`, `letter-spacing: 0` ; ligne-hauteur 17/19/22px selon taille
- **Couleurs primary** : fond `#368e35` → hover `#1D4ED8` → active `#1E40AF` · disabled fond `#F3F4F6` + texte `#D1D5DB`
- **Couleurs secondary** : fond `#FFFFFF` → hover `#F9FAFB` → active `#F3F4F6` · texte `#374151` · bordure `#D1D5DB`
- **Focus ring** : `outline 2px` offset `2px`, couleur `#3B82F6` ; état `disabled` via attribut natif `disabled`

## Do & Don't

✅ **Do**
- Utiliser `primary` pour l'action principale et unique d'une zone.
- Toujours spécifier `type="button"`, `type="submit"` ou `type="reset"` explicitement.
- Transmettre `disabled` comme attribut HTML natif.

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas utiliser `<button>` pour la navigation — préférer un `<a>`.
- Ne pas inventer de variante hors `primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `danger`.
- Ne pas surcharger les CSS vars hors de la liste `allowedCssVars`.

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const sizeTokens = {
  sm: {
    paddingX: 'var(--button-size-sm-padding-x)',
    paddingY: 'var(--button-size-sm-padding-y)',
    fontSize: 'var(--button-size-sm-font-size)',
    lineHeight: 'var(--button-size-sm-line-height)',
    gap: 'var(--button-size-sm-gap)',
    minHeight: 'var(--button-size-sm-min-height)',
    iconSize: 'var(--button-size-sm-icon-size)',
  },
  md: {
    paddingX: 'var(--button-size-md-padding-x)',
    paddingY: 'var(--button-size-md-padding-y)',
    fontSize: 'var(--button-size-md-font-size)',
    lineHeight: 'var(--button-size-md-line-height)',
    gap: 'var(--button-size-md-gap)',
    minHeight: 'var(--button-size-md-min-height)',
    iconSize: 'var(--button-size-md-icon-size)',
  },
  lg: {
    paddingX: 'var(--button-size-lg-padding-x)',
    paddingY: 'var(--button-size-lg-padding-y)',
    fontSize: 'var(--button-size-lg-font-size)',
    lineHeight: 'var(--button-size-lg-line-height)',
    gap: 'var(--button-size-lg-gap)',
    minHeight: 'var(--button-size-lg-min-height)',
    iconSize: 'var(--button-size-lg-icon-size)',
  },
};

const variantTokens = {
  primary: {
    bg: 'var(--color-action-primary-bg-default)',
    bgHover: 'var(--color-action-primary-bg-hover)',
    bgActive: 'var(--color-action-primary-bg-active)',
    bgDisabled: 'var(--color-action-primary-bg-disabled)',
    text: 'var(--color-action-primary-text-default)',
    textDisabled: 'var(--color-action-primary-text-disabled)',
    border: 'var(--color-action-primary-border-default)',
    borderHover: 'var(--color-action-primary-border-hover)',
    borderDisabled: 'var(--color-action-primary-border-disabled)',
  },
  secondary: {
    bg: 'var(--color-action-secondary-bg-default)',
    bgHover: 'var(--color-action-secondary-bg-hover)',
    bgActive: 'var(--color-action-secondary-bg-active)',
    bgDisabled: 'var(--color-action-secondary-bg-disabled)',
    text: 'var(--color-action-secondary-text-default)',
    textDisabled: 'var(--color-action-secondary-text-disabled)',
    border: 'var(--color-action-secondary-border-default)',
    borderHover: 'var(--color-action-secondary-border-hover)',
    borderDisabled: 'var(--color-action-secondary-border-disabled)',
  },
  ghost: {
    bg: 'var(--color-action-ghost-bg-default)',
    bgHover: 'var(--color-action-ghost-bg-hover)',
    bgActive: 'var(--color-action-ghost-bg-active)',
    bgDisabled: 'var(--color-action-ghost-bg-disabled)',
    text: 'var(--color-action-ghost-text-default)',
    textDisabled: 'var(--color-action-ghost-text-disabled)',
    border: 'var(--color-action-ghost-border-default)',
    borderHover: 'var(--color-action-ghost-border-hover)',
    borderDisabled: 'var(--color-action-ghost-border-disabled)',
  },
  danger: {
    bg: 'var(--color-action-danger-bg-default)',
    bgHover: 'var(--color-action-danger-bg-hover)',
    bgActive: 'var(--color-action-danger-bg-active)',
    bgDisabled: 'var(--color-action-danger-bg-disabled)',
    text: 'var(--color-action-danger-text-default)',
    textDisabled: 'var(--color-action-danger-text-disabled)',
    border: 'var(--color-action-danger-border-default)',
    borderHover: 'var(--color-action-danger-border-hover)',
    borderDisabled: 'var(--color-action-danger-border-disabled)',
  },
};

function Button({ children, variant = 'primary', size = 'md', disabled = false, onClick, type = 'button', icon }) {
  const [hovered, setHovered] = React.useState(false);
  const [active, setActive] = React.useState(false);

  const s = sizeTokens[size];
  const v = variantTokens[variant];

  const bg = disabled ? v.bgDisabled : active ? v.bgActive : hovered ? v.bgHover : v.bg;
  const color = disabled ? v.textDisabled : v.text;
  const borderColor = disabled ? v.borderDisabled : hovered ? v.borderHover : v.border;

  return (
    <button
      type={type}
      disabled={disabled}
      onClick={onClick}
      onMouseEnter={() => !disabled && setHovered(true)}
      onMouseLeave={() => { setHovered(false); setActive(false); }}
      onMouseDown={() => !disabled && setActive(true)}
      onMouseUp={() => setActive(false)}
      style={{
        display: 'inline-flex',
        alignItems: 'center',
        justifyContent: 'center',
        gap: s.gap,
        paddingTop: s.paddingY,
        paddingBottom: s.paddingY,
        paddingLeft: s.paddingX,
        paddingRight: s.paddingX,
        minHeight: s.minHeight,
        fontSize: s.fontSize,
        lineHeight: s.lineHeight,
        fontWeight: 'var(--button-font-weight)',
        fontFamily: 'var(--button-font-family)',
        borderRadius: 'var(--button-radius)',
        borderWidth: 'var(--button-border-width)',
        borderStyle: 'solid',
        borderColor,
        background: bg,
        color,
        cursor: disabled ? 'not-allowed' : 'pointer',
        transition: 'var(--button-transition)',
        outline: 'none',
        boxSizing: 'border-box',
      }}
      onFocus={e => {
        e.currentTarget.style.outline = `var(--button-focus-ring-width) solid var(--button-focus-ring-color)`;
        e.currentTarget.style.outlineOffset = 'var(--button-focus-ring-offset)';
      }}
      onBlur={e => {
        e.currentTarget.style.outline = 'none';
      }}
    >
      {icon && (
        <span style={{ width: s.iconSize, height: s.iconSize, display: 'inline-flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}>
          {icon}
        </span>
      )}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}

const IconPlus = ({ size }) => (
  <svg width={size || 12} height={size || 12} viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
    <path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5" strokeLinecap="round"/>
  </svg>
);

render(
  <div style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--button-font-family)', padding: '24px', background: '#f8f9fa' }}>
    <div className="grid gap-8">
      {['primary', 'secondary', 'ghost', 'danger'].map(variant => (
        <div key={variant}>
          <p style={{ fontSize: 11, fontWeight: 600, textTransform: 'uppercase', letterSpacing: '0.08em', color: '#6B7280', marginBottom: 12 }}>
            {variant}
          </p>
          <div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
            {['sm', 'md', 'lg'].map(size => (
              <Button key={size} variant={variant} size={size} type="button">
                Button
              </Button>
            ))}
            <Button variant={variant} size="md" type="button" icon={<IconPlus />}>
              With icon
            </Button>
            <Button variant={variant} size="md" type="button" disabled>
              Disabled
            </Button>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

input.description:
## Description
Champ de saisie texte (`<input>`) supportant trois tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`) et quatre états (`default`, `focus`, `error`, `disabled`). Les tokens de couleur, espacement et typographie sont appliqués via variables CSS.

## Spec
- La spec Figma n'est pas disponible (`figma.available === false`, `designSpec === null`) — les valeurs visuelles proviennent exclusivement des tokens du contrat MCP.
- Trois tailles : `sm` (minHeight 32px, fontSize 14px), `md` (minHeight 40px, fontSize 16px), `lg` (minHeight 48px, fontSize 18px).
- Radius uniforme : `--input-radius` → 8px ; border-width : `--input-border-width` → 1px.
- Background : `--input-bg-default` (#FFF) / `--input-bg-disabled` (#F3F4F6).
- Bordure : default `--input-border-default`, hover `--input-border-hover`, focus `--input-border-focus` (#3B82F6), error `--input-border-error` (#EF4444), disabled `--input-border-disabled`.
- Couleur de texte : `--input-text-default` / placeholder `--input-text-placeholder` / disabled `--input-text-disabled`.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Associer un `<label>` via `htmlFor` / `id` à chaque champ.
- Afficher un message d'erreur textuel sous le champ en complément de la couleur rouge.
- Utiliser uniquement les tailles `sm`, `md`, `lg` déclarées dans le contrat.

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas transformer ce composant en `<textarea>` ou `<select>`.
- Ne pas inventer un état non prévu (`success`, `warning`, etc.).
- Ne pas remplacer le `<label>` par le seul `placeholder`.

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const sizeTokens = {
  sm: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-sm-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-sm-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-sm-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-sm-min-height)",
  },
  md: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-md-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-md-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-md-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-md-min-height)",
  },
  lg: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-lg-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-lg-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-lg-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-lg-min-height)",
  },
};

const stateBorderColor = {
  default: "var(--input-border-default)",
  focus: "var(--input-border-focus)",
  error: "var(--input-border-error)",
  disabled: "var(--input-border-disabled)",
};

const Input = ({ size = "md", state = "default", placeholder, value, onChange, type = "text", name, id }) => {
  const tok = sizeTokens[size];
  const isDisabled = state === "disabled";

  return (
    <input
      type={type}
      name={name}
      id={id}
      placeholder={placeholder}
      value={value}
      onChange={onChange}
      disabled={isDisabled}
      style={{
        display: "block",
        width: "100%",
        minHeight: tok.minHeight,
        paddingInline: tok.paddingX,
        paddingBlock: tok.paddingY,
        fontSize: tok.fontSize,
        fontFamily: "inherit",
        lineHeight: "1.5",
        color: isDisabled ? "var(--input-text-disabled)" : "var(--input-text-default)",
        background: isDisabled ? "var(--input-bg-disabled)" : "var(--input-bg-default)",
        border: `var(--input-border-width) solid ${stateBorderColor[state]}`,
        borderRadius: "var(--input-radius)",
        outline: state === "focus" ? `2px solid var(--input-border-focus)` : "none",
        outlineOffset: "2px",
        boxSizing: "border-box",
        cursor: isDisabled ? "not-allowed" : "text",
        opacity: isDisabled ? "0.5" : "1",
      }}
    />
  );
};

const SIZES = ["sm", "md", "lg"];
const STATES = ["default", "focus", "error", "disabled"];

const placeholderByState = {
  default: "Valeur par défaut",
  focus:   "État focus",
  error:   "Valeur invalide",
  disabled:"Champ désactivé",
};

render(
  <div className="p-6 bg-white space-y-8">
    {SIZES.map((size) => (
      <div key={size}>
        <p className="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">
          Size — {size}
        </p>
        <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-4">
          {STATES.map((state) => (
            <div key={state} className="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <label
                htmlFor={`input-${size}-${state}`}
                style={{
                  fontSize: "12px",
                  color: state === "error" ? "var(--color-danger-500)" : "var(--color-text-primary)",
                  marginBottom: "4px",
                }}
              >
                {state.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + state.slice(1)}
              </label>
              <Input
                id={`input-${size}-${state}`}
                size={size}
                state={state}
                placeholder={placeholderByState[state]}
                type="text"
              />
              {state === "error" && (
                <span style={{ fontSize: "12px", color: "var(--color-danger-500)" }}>
                  Ce champ est requis.
                </span>
              )}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
);
```

card.description:
## Description
Conteneur de contenu sémantique (`<article>`) avec padding, rayon de coin et élévation pilotables par tokens. Disponible en 3 variantes (`default`, `elevated`, `outline`) et 3 tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`).

## Spec
- **Dimensions Figma** : largeur fixe 400px, hauteur 540px pour les composants enfants du set ; le COMPONENT_SET fait 908×592px
- **Border-radius** : `8px` (cornerRadius Figma) → token `--card-radius` résolu à `12px` (le token contract prime comme source de vérité contractuelle)
- **Background** : `#ffffff` (SOLID fill) → token `--card-bg`
- **Drop-shadow** : `0px 0px 6px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.25)` (Figma) — token contrat `--card-shadow` résolu à `0 1px 2px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.05)` (shadow.100) ; variante `elevated` utilise `--shadow-200`
- **Layout interne** : direction column, alignItems flex-start, gap non spécifié dans Figma → on utilise uniquement les tokens disponibles
- **Bordure** : absente sur les enfants Figma (strokes vides) ; appliquée via `--card-border` pour la variante `outline` uniquement

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser `<article>` ou `<section>` selon le contexte sémantique du contenu
- Regrouper un contenu homogène et hiérarchiquement cohérent dans la card
- Choisir la variante `elevated` pour mettre en avant une card dans une grille

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas utiliser la card comme bouton ou élément cliquable interactif
- Ne pas imbriquer plus de deux niveaux de cards
- Ne pas utiliser de variables CSS hors de la liste `allowedCssVars`

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const paddingMap = {
  sm: "var(--card-padding-sm)",
  md: "var(--card-padding-md)",
  lg: "var(--card-padding-lg)",
};

const shadowMap = {
  default: "var(--card-shadow)",
  elevated: "var(--shadow-200)",
  outline: "none",
};

const borderMap = {
  default: "none",
  elevated: "none",
  outline: "1px solid var(--card-border)",
};

function Card({ size = "md", variant = "default", children, className = "" }) {
  return (
    <article
      className={className}
      style={{
        background: "var(--card-bg)",
        borderRadius: "var(--card-radius)",
        padding: paddingMap[size],
        boxShadow: shadowMap[variant],
        border: borderMap[variant],
        display: "flex",
        flexDirection: "column",
        gap: "12px",
        width: "280px",
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </article>
  );
}

function CardContent({ title, body, size }) {
  const titleSize = { sm: "13px", md: "15px", lg: "18px" }[size];
  const bodySize  = { sm: "11px", md: "13px", lg: "15px" }[size];
  return (
    <>
      <strong style={{ fontSize: titleSize, color: "#111827", margin: 0 }}>
        {title}
      </strong>
      <p style={{ fontSize: bodySize, color: "#6B7280", margin: 0, lineHeight: 1.5 }}>
        {body}
      </p>
    </>
  );
}

const variants = ["default", "elevated", "outline"];
const sizes    = ["sm", "md", "lg"];

const meta = {
  default:  { title: "Card Default",   body: "Contenu standard sans élévation marquée." },
  elevated: { title: "Card Elevated",  body: "Mise en avant avec ombre renforcée." },
  outline:  { title: "Card Outline",   body: "Délimitée par une bordure, sans ombre." },
};

render(
  <div className="p-8 bg-gray-100 min-h-screen">
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {sizes.map((size) =>
        variants.map((variant) => (
          <div key={`${size}-${variant}`} className="flex flex-col items-start gap-2">
            <span className="text-xs text-gray-400 font-mono uppercase tracking-wide">
              {variant} / {size}
            </span>
            <Card size={size} variant={variant}>
              <CardContent
                title={meta[variant].title}
                body={meta[variant].body}
                size={size}
              />
            </Card>
          </div>
        ))
      )}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

badge.description:
## Description
Étiquette compacte (`<span>`) non interactive pour afficher un statut, une catégorie ou une métadonnée visuelle. Supporte 6 variantes de couleur sémantique.

## Spec
- La spec Figma n'est pas disponible (`figma.available === false`, `designSpec === null`) — les valeurs visuelles sont issues exclusivement du contrat MCP (`contract.componentTokens` et `contract.referencedTokens`).
- **Padding** : `--badge-padding-x` (8px) en inline, `--badge-padding-y` (4px) en block.
- **Typographie** : `--badge-font-size` (12px), `--badge-font-weight` (500).
- **Border-radius** : `--badge-radius` (9999px → pilule).
- **6 variantes** : `primary`, `secondary`, `success`, `warning`, `danger`, `neutral` — chacune avec fond et texte dédiés.
- **Props acceptées** : `variant`, `children`, `icon` (slot optionnel avant le libellé).

## Do & Don't

✅ **Do**
- Utiliser pour un label court (statut, catégorie, compteur).
- Choisir la variante sémantique adaptée au contexte (success, warning, danger…).
- Conserver un contenu très court, idéalement 1 à 3 mots.

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas utiliser comme bouton ou élément interactif cliquable.
- Ne pas y placer des phrases longues ou du contenu riche.
- Ne pas inventer de taille ou d'état non déclarés dans le contrat MCP.

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const variantTokens = {
  primary: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-primary-bg-default)",
    color: "var(--color-action-primary-text-default)",
  },
  secondary: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-secondary-bg-default)",
    color: "var(--color-action-secondary-text-default)",
  },
  success: {
    bg: "var(--color-feedback-success-bg)",
    color: "var(--color-feedback-success-text)",
  },
  warning: {
    bg: "var(--color-feedback-warning-bg)",
    color: "var(--color-feedback-warning-text)",
  },
  danger: {
    bg: "var(--color-feedback-error-bg)",
    color: "var(--color-feedback-error-text)",
  },
  neutral: {
    bg: "var(--color-neutral-100)",
    color: "var(--color-neutral-800)",
  },
};

const Badge = ({ variant = "neutral", icon, children }) => {
  const tokens = variantTokens[variant] ?? variantTokens.neutral;

  return (
    <span
      style={{
        display: "inline-flex",
        alignItems: "center",
        gap: "var(--badge-padding-y)",
        paddingInline: "var(--badge-padding-x)",
        paddingBlock: "var(--badge-padding-y)",
        fontSize: "var(--badge-font-size)",
        fontWeight: "var(--badge-font-weight)",
        borderRadius: "var(--badge-radius)",
        backgroundColor: tokens.bg,
        color: tokens.color,
        lineHeight: 1,
        whiteSpace: "nowrap",
      }}
    >
      {icon && <span aria-hidden="true">{icon}</span>}
      {children}
    </span>
  );
};

render(
  <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-4 p-6 items-center">
    <Badge variant="primary">Primary</Badge>
    <Badge variant="secondary">Secondary</Badge>
    <Badge variant="success">Success</Badge>
    <Badge variant="warning">Warning</Badge>
    <Badge variant="danger">Danger</Badge>
    <Badge variant="neutral">Neutral</Badge>
    <Badge variant="success" icon="✓">Vérifié</Badge>
    <Badge variant="danger" icon="✕">Rejeté</Badge>
    <Badge variant="warning" icon="⚠">En attente</Badge>
  </div>
);
```
